ing: 2 tablespoons coconut aminos teriyaki sauce, divided
1/2 large green bell pepper, thinly sliced
1 large zucchini, cut into long strands
des: "This is a paleo-friendly, gluten-free Asian-inspired zoodle recipe. Don't worry about going back for seconds with all those veggies! This is my new go-to!"
ins: Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon teriyaki sauce in a large skillet over medium heat. Add carrot, bell pepper, and onion; cook and stir until onions are translucent, about 5 minutes. Stir in bok choy, zucchini, and garlic powder. Drizzle on remaining teriyaki sauce. Cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender, about 7 minutes.
